
[1]martingal

   M`ARTINGAL, n.

   1. A strap or thong fastened to the girth under a horse's belly, and at
   the other end to the muss-roll, passing between the fore legs.

   2. In ships, a rope extending from the jibboom, to the end of a bumpkin
   under the cap of the bowsprit.
